{
  "stem": "4670.3",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "They had separated, and then divorced.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "He came to Chicago.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And her two daughters had come.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "One had come directly to the United States, and one, the daughter Ruth, had gone to Holland first.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And I think, because of that, things changed for her.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "She decided to take a chance.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "We heard all this later.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "This was not immediately.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "She had taken a-- she had gone on a ship called the St.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "Louis, which was leaving Hamburg in 1939.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "It was supposed to be leaving on the May 13, 1939.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "But before it left, it was going to Havana, Cuba.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "There were close to 1,000 people aboard ship.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "There were 936 passengers, actually. 930 were Jewish.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "But there was a very corrupt immigration officer in Havana and he had collected the landing certificate from every single person on this ship.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "He had collected $160, which was a lot of money.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And he had pocketed that money.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And the officials that worked with him realized that and they put up-- apparently, they let the government know.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And so the government just decided that the ship was not going to land, that the people should have visas.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "But since the people had bought their landing certificates before this new edict in Cuba, apparently, the Hamburg America line, you know, the German ship line, thought it was safe.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And so did the people.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "The passengers thought it was safe.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "They had no reason not to believe that.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "And they got aboard ship on the 13th of May, and the ship traveled to Havana.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "And when they got to Havana, the president of Cuba would not let them get off the ship.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
